11:46.421 --> 11:47.555
That's not enough time.

11:47.589 --> 11:49.023
You won't be doing it alone.

11:49.057 --> 11:51.025
I've asked Reggie to help you.

11:52.360 --> 11:54.795
REGGIE: I'm not just gonna help you.
I'm gonna do it for you.

11:54.829 --> 11:56.330
You're gonna extract me from my own con?

11:56.364 --> 11:57.798
Yes, I am, and do you know why?

11:57.832 --> 11:59.567
Because you don't trust me to do it.

11:59.601 --> 12:01.202
No! 'Cause I love you.

12:01.236 --> 12:03.137
All right, Reggie, I think that's...

12:03.171 --> 12:05.973
No, no, you're so good.
You're so method that,

12:06.007 --> 12:07.675
when you take on a con,
you become that guy.

12:07.709 --> 12:09.076
- Mnh.
- I mean, look at you.

12:09.110 --> 12:12.513
You have become this fine,
upstanding citizen,

12:12.547 --> 12:15.849
who all he wants to do is marry
the redheaded lady detective

12:15.884 --> 12:18.052
and settle down.

12:18.086 --> 12:20.287
You are not that guy.

12:21.556 --> 12:24.391
You think I don't know
about your little game?

12:24.426 --> 12:27.728
"Are you ready to play?"

12:27.762 --> 12:32.299
It's not just your life you're
playing with here, Ben.

12:33.301 --> 12:38.405
So, tomorrow morning, after
you kiss her goodbye,

12:38.440 --> 12:40.941
I'm gonna let myself into her house,

12:40.976 --> 12:46.513
and I will make every
trace of you disappear...

12:46.548 --> 12:50.217
DNA, fingerprints, all of it...

12:50.252 --> 12:54.722
gone, like Christopher
Hall never existed...

12:54.756 --> 12:58.125
which he never did...

12:58.159 --> 12:58.926
right?

13:04.501 --> 13:06.502
What is this?

13:06.537 --> 13:09.005
It's a very simple,
tasteful, white dress.

13:09.039 --> 13:10.240
[Gasps]

13:10.274 --> 13:12.542
You gonna put it on for me,
give me a little private show?

13:12.576 --> 13:15.178
I thought you no longer believed
in the institution of marriage.

13:15.212 --> 13:16.412
I believe in the institution

13:16.447 --> 13:18.982
of a fine, well-tailored garment
no matter what the occasion.

13:19.016 --> 13:19.849
Try it on.

13:19.884 --> 13:20.650
[Chuckling] No.

13:20.684 --> 13:21.484
You know you want to.

13:21.518 --> 13:22.385
Val.

13:22.419 --> 13:24.754
All right.

13:24.788 --> 13:30.026
But between the cake and the dress,

13:30.060 --> 13:33.429
somebody doesn't seem very
excited about her wedding.

13:33.464 --> 13:34.764
Can I tell you something?

13:34.798 --> 13:35.932
- What?
- I'm not.

13:35.966 --> 13:38.534
I'm excited to be married.

13:38.569 --> 13:40.837
I just kind of hate weddings.

13:40.871 --> 13:42.839
[Gasps] You hated my wedding?

13:42.873 --> 13:46.175
No! I hated me at your wedding...
at any wedding.

13:46.210 --> 13:47.377
I'm terrible at them.

13:47.411 --> 13:49.012
I never know what to do at a weddings

13:49.046 --> 13:50.713
except drink too much and sleep with

13:50.748 --> 13:52.515
inappropriate people [gasps]
which you're not allowed to do

13:52.549 --> 13:53.883
at your own wedding.

13:53.918 --> 13:54.951
Who did you sleep with at my wedding?

13:54.985 --> 13:56.519
No one.

13:56.553 --> 13:57.854
Bartender.

13:57.888 --> 13:59.622
[Both laugh]

13:59.657 --> 14:02.058
Which is proof that I am
terrible at weddings.

14:02.092 --> 14:03.192
I don't know.

14:03.227 --> 14:05.561
Sounds like you had more fun
at my wedding than I did.

14:08.732 --> 14:10.900
And if you really hated weddings...

14:10.935 --> 14:14.370
you would have never bought
yourself this dress.

14:14.405 --> 14:16.372
It is a good dress.

14:19.310 --> 14:21.110
♪ Don't wake me up ♪

14:21.145 --> 14:27.250
♪ I'm trying to find you ♪

14:27.284 --> 14:30.920
♪ Oh, as I walk through ♪

14:30.955 --> 14:36.893
♪ You're hiding in the
corners of my mind ♪

14:36.927 --> 14:38.728
♪ Never fear ♪

14:38.762 --> 14:40.063
Alice, honey, you home?

14:40.097 --> 14:41.798
Just a sec! Don't come in!

14:41.832 --> 14:44.233
Go away! Don't look.

14:44.268 --> 14:45.201
It's bad luck.

14:45.235 --> 14:48.905
♪ My only love, I'll follow behind you ♪

14:48.939 --> 14:52.575
Honey, please.

14:52.609 --> 14:54.277
♪ I won't go without you ♪

14:54.311 --> 14:56.412
Let me see.

14:56.447 --> 15:01.985
♪ I know your love weighs
heavy on my heart ♪

15:02.019 --> 15:07.757
♪ But you are my only counterpart ♪

15:07.791 --> 15:08.858
What do you think?

15:08.892 --> 15:10.860
♪ Well, I know ♪

15:10.894 --> 15:14.130
[Exhales sharply]

15:14.164 --> 15:20.203
♪ Why I lost control ♪

15:20.237 --> 15:21.771
♪ Of my heart and soul ♪

15:21.805 --> 15:25.174
I think...

15:25.209 --> 15:27.043
you should take it off...

15:27.077 --> 15:29.379
♪ Because I know you ♪

15:29.413 --> 15:30.279
...right now.

15:30.314 --> 15:33.516
♪ I can reach through ♪

15:33.550 --> 15:37.120
♪ I-I-I made mistakes ♪

15:37.154 --> 15:42.892
♪ But they're safely behind me ♪

15:42.926 --> 15:46.996
♪ Now I can run free ♪

15:47.031 --> 15:53.002
♪ The only true love I have ever known ♪

15:53.037 --> 15:59.008
♪ Oh, I know-ow ♪

15:59.043 --> 16:00.510
♪ Oh, oh, ah ♪

16:00.544 --> 16:03.813
♪ Don't wake me up ♪

16:03.847 --> 16:08.017
♪ I'm trying to find you ♪

16:12.890 --> 16:15.658
What? What's wrong?

16:15.692 --> 16:19.128
[Sighs]

16:21.532 --> 16:22.965
I have something to tell you.

16:29.473 --> 16:31.274
[Sighs]

16:31.308 --> 16:34.544
Alice...

16:34.578 --> 16:38.915
[Sighs]

16:41.318 --> 16:44.420
[Inhales sharply, chuckles]

16:44.455 --> 16:47.056
[Chuckles]

16:47.091 --> 16:48.724
You know what I want to do?

16:48.759 --> 16:49.692
I want to run away.

16:49.726 --> 16:50.159
What?

16:50.194 --> 16:51.127
So let's do it.

16:51.161 --> 16:52.128
[Laughing] What?

16:52.162 --> 16:53.062
Let's go away.

16:53.097 --> 16:55.131
We'll go to City Hall,
and we'll get married.

16:55.165 --> 16:56.599
Then we'll get on a plane,
and we will just go.

16:56.633 --> 16:57.934
We'll go wherever you want to go.

16:57.968 --> 16:59.035
[Laughs]

16:59.069 --> 17:00.269
You want to go to the Riviera?
We'll go to the Riviera.

17:00.304 --> 17:04.140
You want to go to the Serengeti,
the Swiss Alps... you name it.

17:04.174 --> 17:05.308
Okay? We'll go where no one can find us.

17:05.342 --> 17:06.909
Where is this coming from?

17:06.944 --> 17:09.811
I just... I want you.

17:09.847 --> 17:12.147
That's it. I want you.

17:12.182 --> 17:13.749
I don't need the rest of it.

17:13.784 --> 17:15.952
I don't want the rest of it, any of it.

17:15.986 --> 17:18.154
But we have to go now.
We have to leave today.

17:18.188 --> 17:20.223
Sweetheart, I can't just go.

17:20.257 --> 17:20.957
Yes, you can.

17:20.991 --> 17:22.157
I have this case.

17:22.192 --> 17:23.960
Yes, you can. You can do this.

17:23.993 --> 17:25.228
We can do this.

17:25.262 --> 17:29.398
[Sighs]

17:29.433 --> 17:31.767
Okay.

17:31.802 --> 17:33.102
Okay.

17:33.137 --> 17:36.973
The minute I catch this
guy, I'm all yours.

17:47.184 --> 17:49.152
I love you.

17:49.186 --> 17:51.954
You know that, right?

17:51.989 --> 17:55.591
Mm-hmm.

17:59.897 --> 18:01.097
[Sighs]

18:06.069 --> 18:09.338
See you tonight.

18:09.373 --> 18:13.442
Bye.

18:22.219 --> 18:25.154
Mr. X has hit us three times
in the last nine months,

18:25.189 --> 18:26.422
the same crime done in the same way

18:26.456 --> 18:29.125
and always within a few hours
of sending us the same note...

18:29.159 --> 18:30.193
"Are you ready to play?"

18:30.227 --> 18:33.396
So I'm thinking this guy
either wants to get caught

18:33.430 --> 18:35.865
or he really loves playing this game.

18:35.899 --> 18:36.866
But games have rules.

18:36.900 --> 18:39.335
So, if we can figure out
what his rules are,

18:39.369 --> 18:43.472
we may actually stand a
chance of catching him.

18:43.507 --> 18:44.874
Are you okay?

18:44.908 --> 18:47.176
[Inhales sharply, sighs]

18:47.211 --> 18:49.312
Christopher asked me
to elope this morning.

18:49.346 --> 18:51.047
- He what?
- Oh, my gosh, Alice.

18:51.081 --> 18:53.716
Yeah. He wanted me to just
get on a plane with him

18:53.750 --> 18:54.884
and go to the Alps.

18:54.918 --> 18:55.918
And you didn't go?

18:55.953 --> 18:56.986
I have a job.

18:57.020 --> 18:58.588
Oh, get out right now.

18:58.622 --> 18:59.889
Val.

18:59.923 --> 19:01.190
I am serious.

19:01.225 --> 19:06.329
Honey... he asked you
to marry him on an Alp.

19:08.068 --> 19:09.601
<i>You've reached Christopher Hall.</i>

19:09.636 --> 19:11.336
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

19:11.371 --> 19:13.605
How do you feel about the
Palace Hotel in Gstaad?

19:13.640 --> 19:15.908
I'm going home to pack. Call me.

19:15.942 --> 19:17.976
[Water running]

19:57.016 --> 19:58.250
[Sighs]

20:07.293 --> 20:09.128
<i>You've reached Christopher Hall.</i>

20:09.162 --> 20:11.130
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

20:13.133 --> 20:17.069
[Horn honks, tires screech]

20:17.103 --> 20:20.038
<i>WOMAN: I'm sorry. The number you
have reached has been disconnected.</i>

20:21.674 --> 20:23.142
[Tires screech]

20:26.212 --> 20:28.814
He's gone. Christopher is gone.

20:28.848 --> 20:29.982
What do you mean?

20:30.016 --> 20:33.418
His clothes, his shampoo,
his toothbrush, everything.

20:33.453 --> 20:35.721
I'm at his office now.

20:55.975 --> 20:57.943
Gone.

21:03.077 --> 21:04.645
I gave him all of my money,

21:04.670 --> 21:06.107
$1.4 million,

21:06.225 --> 21:07.993
my entire life savings.

21:08.027 --> 21:10.262
I didn't give it to the Realtor.

21:10.296 --> 21:11.496
I gave it to him.

21:11.531 --> 21:12.264
What is wrong with me?

21:12.298 --> 21:13.966
There's nothing wrong with you.

21:14.000 --> 21:15.434
There's nothing wrong with you.

21:15.468 --> 21:17.497
This guy was good... like, really good.

21:17.522 --> 21:18.288
Danny...

21:18.323 --> 21:19.959
His entire web presence is gone...

21:20.024 --> 21:22.192
no archived search items, no photos.

21:22.226 --> 21:23.726
I don't even know how
to start investigating.

21:23.761 --> 21:24.727
I have photos.

21:24.762 --> 21:25.995
[Keyboard clacking]

21:26.030 --> 21:28.131
I have photos.

21:35.272 --> 21:36.506
Oh, my God.

21:40.406 --> 21:41.406
He never looks at the camera.

21:43.376 --> 21:44.910
He was hiding the entire time.

21:46.913 --> 21:47.746
Would this help?

21:47.780 --> 21:50.282
Thank you, Sophie.

21:50.316 --> 21:51.850
[Keyboard clacking]

21:55.955 --> 21:57.856
Hey...

21:57.890 --> 21:59.190
do you want to go home?

21:59.225 --> 22:00.358
Do you want me to come with you?

22:00.393 --> 22:02.394
No. I want to find him.

22:02.428 --> 22:04.229
We will.

22:04.263 --> 22:05.563
I want to do it today, now.

22:09.001 --> 22:12.070
This is what we do, right?

22:12.104 --> 22:14.472
So...

22:14.507 --> 22:16.441
what do we know

22:16.475 --> 22:23.448
about Christopher Hall?

22:23.482 --> 22:26.217
[Sighs]

22:26.252 --> 22:28.119
Nothing.

22:28.154 --> 22:30.055
We know nothing about Christopher Hall

22:30.089 --> 22:33.024
because Christopher Hall doesn't exist.

22:36.429 --> 22:39.597
Maybe start with what you do know.

22:39.632 --> 22:43.401
How did you guys meet?

22:43.436 --> 22:44.803
[Sighs]

22:44.837 --> 22:46.338
He came in as a client.

22:46.372 --> 22:49.074
He said that Seth
Hamilton recommended us.

22:50.042 --> 22:51.476
Alice is our lead investigator.

22:51.510 --> 22:53.278
Valerie actually runs the company

22:53.312 --> 22:54.646
so I can be out in the field.

22:54.680 --> 22:56.448
We're private investigators, but we...

22:56.482 --> 22:59.484
We also provide personal
and corporate security.

22:59.518 --> 23:01.119
Which is what you're doing for Seth.

23:01.153 --> 23:03.455
And a number of high-profile clients.

23:05.224 --> 23:09.594
The guy's last V.C. deal
was worth $400 million.

23:09.628 --> 23:10.762
He's going with another firm.

23:10.796 --> 23:11.930
What?

23:11.964 --> 23:13.198
Did he say why?

23:13.232 --> 23:15.800
He said that we're not a good fit.

23:15.835 --> 23:22.107
♪ Your arms are weary, but
you're trying to learn this ♪

23:24.210 --> 23:26.511
Ms. Vaughan. This is a coincidence.

23:26.545 --> 23:27.612
It's not, actually.

23:27.646 --> 23:29.848
I made a few calls, found
out where you were dining

23:29.882 --> 23:31.616
and that you were dining
alone, so I thought...

23:31.650 --> 23:33.051
You thought you'd demonstrate

23:33.085 --> 23:34.719
your firm's investigative prowess?

23:34.754 --> 23:36.554
Is that how you landed Seth Hamilton?

23:36.589 --> 23:37.822
I didn't have to do much.

23:37.857 --> 23:39.524
Your secretary is very chatty.

23:39.558 --> 23:41.526
She's not gonna be my
secretary much longer.

23:41.560 --> 23:43.561
Our firm is happy to vet
new candidates for you...

23:43.596 --> 23:46.364
unless, of course, you think
we're aren't a good fit.

23:48.000 --> 23:49.200
Will the lady be joining?

23:50.002 --> 23:51.369
Mm.

23:53.506 --> 23:55.240
Thank you.

23:55.274 --> 23:57.542
You really should have
let me pay for dinner.

23:57.576 --> 23:59.844
If I'd let you pay, it
would make this next part

23:59.879 --> 24:03.415
of the conversation...
very uncomfortable.

24:03.449 --> 24:05.583
You're going with the other firm.

24:05.618 --> 24:06.985
May I ask why?

24:07.019 --> 24:08.153
There's a conflict of interest.

24:08.187 --> 24:10.321
What's the conflict?

24:10.356 --> 24:12.824
I am interested in seeing
one of the partners

24:12.858 --> 24:14.325
outside the office.

24:14.360 --> 24:15.160
Is it Danny?

24:15.194 --> 24:17.896
Because Danny's only an associate.

24:17.930 --> 24:19.898
It's not Danny.

24:19.932 --> 24:22.901
♪ To love you

24:22.935 --> 24:25.403
Unless you think we're not a good fit.

24:26.705 --> 24:29.441
It was a textbook con. I approached him.

24:29.475 --> 24:30.275
SOPHIE: How do you mean?

24:30.309 --> 24:31.409
A con man never approaches a mark.

24:31.444 --> 24:33.578
He creates a situation where
the mark approaches him,

24:33.612 --> 24:34.913
where the mark wants something from him.

24:34.947 --> 24:36.748
I wanted his firm's business.

24:36.782 --> 24:38.850
And because we ended up dating,
he never became a client,

24:38.884 --> 24:40.418
so we never really vetted him.

24:40.453 --> 24:42.420
There was no need. He seemed perfect.

24:42.455 --> 24:46.891
♪ Why's it scare me to love you? ♪

24:46.926 --> 24:47.926
I'm so sorry.

24:47.960 --> 24:49.294
BEN: Aw, don't be.

24:49.328 --> 24:51.262
I am sick of eating in restaurants,

24:51.297 --> 24:52.730
and you know how much
I hate other people.

24:52.765 --> 24:55.800
[Chuckles]

24:55.835 --> 24:56.468
Is that it?

24:56.502 --> 24:58.436
Mm-hmm.

25:03.409 --> 25:07.245
Wow. You're right. That is amazing.

25:07.279 --> 25:10.482
Oh.

25:10.516 --> 25:11.416
What?

25:11.450 --> 25:12.817
Well, I've been wondering
what to get you

25:12.852 --> 25:14.085
for a wedding present. Oh, come on.

25:14.120 --> 25:16.788
It's a museum piece.
It's worth a fortune.

25:16.822 --> 25:18.556
Even you can't afford it.

25:18.591 --> 25:19.390
Mnh.

25:19.425 --> 25:20.959
You really like it?

25:20.993 --> 25:22.961
Mm-hmm.

25:22.995 --> 25:28.566
I know exactly how he feels.

25:28.601 --> 25:31.169
♪ You won't stay over

25:31.203 --> 25:32.470
♪ Now you've been left holding

25:32.505 --> 25:36.674
No, you work. I'll be right over there.

25:36.709 --> 25:39.777
ALICE: A con man gives and gives.
He never takes...

25:39.812 --> 25:42.180
to establish trust and make
the mark dependent on him

25:42.214 --> 25:43.615
so the mark keeps coming back.

25:43.649 --> 25:45.483
He never asks for anything...

25:45.518 --> 25:48.419
so you give him everything.

25:50.856 --> 25:53.291
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh

25:53.325 --> 25:56.094
♪ To light this fire

25:56.128 --> 25:58.530
Ms. Vaughan, I thought
you had work to do.

25:58.564 --> 26:01.699
Mnh-mnh.

26:01.734 --> 26:02.500
Mmm.

26:02.535 --> 26:04.435
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh

26:04.470 --> 26:06.271
SOPHIE: The whole time
you were together,

26:06.305 --> 26:07.672
he never asked you for anything?

26:07.706 --> 26:08.606
Not that I can remember.

26:08.641 --> 26:09.507
VALERIE: He did, though.

26:09.542 --> 26:11.943
He asked you to marry him.

26:11.977 --> 26:13.511
[Indistinct conversations]

26:13.546 --> 26:15.446
[Bell chimes]

26:15.481 --> 26:16.381
They're so young.

26:16.415 --> 26:19.050
Maybe you have to be
that young to do it...

26:19.084 --> 26:20.618
to think it's all gonna work out.

26:20.653 --> 26:21.953
Are we that old and jaded?

26:21.987 --> 26:23.288
Well, I am.

26:23.322 --> 26:24.389
Yeah. Me too.

26:24.423 --> 26:27.325
♪ In the ocean

26:32.398 --> 26:34.332
You ever want to get married?

26:34.366 --> 26:35.700
Mm... yeah.

26:35.734 --> 26:36.534
Yeah?

26:36.569 --> 26:38.536
I mean, in theory.

26:38.571 --> 26:41.139
I guess I just never met the right guy.

26:41.173 --> 26:42.040
I'll try not to take that personally.

26:42.074 --> 26:45.510
[Chuckles]
I wasn't talking about you.

26:45.544 --> 26:48.646
So, if I were the right
guy, you would marry me.

26:48.681 --> 26:50.381
- Mnh.
- You wouldn't?

26:50.416 --> 26:52.217
No. That's not what I'm saying.
- So you would.

26:52.251 --> 26:54.319
♪ Why's it scare me to love you? ♪

26:54.353 --> 26:56.321
And what about you?

26:56.355 --> 26:58.223
What about me?

26:58.257 --> 26:58.923
Would you?

26:58.958 --> 27:00.558
Would I what?

27:00.593 --> 27:01.859
Marry me.

27:01.894 --> 27:03.695
Did you just ask me to marry you?

27:03.729 --> 27:05.196
[Laughing] Oh, my God.

27:05.231 --> 27:05.730
You did.

27:05.764 --> 27:08.333
[Laughs] I'm sorry.

27:08.367 --> 27:10.902
Hmm. No. It's all right.

27:10.936 --> 27:13.871
I just, uh...

27:13.906 --> 27:14.672
Well, let me think about it.

27:17.643 --> 27:18.743
I proposed to myself.

27:18.777 --> 27:20.678
SOPHIE: Can I ask a thing?

27:20.713 --> 27:23.681
Why would a con artist target
a private investigator,

27:23.716 --> 27:25.750
the one person most
likely to bring him down?

27:30.122 --> 27:32.890
Danny, check our security protocols.

27:32.925 --> 27:34.525
What am I looking for?

27:34.560 --> 27:36.594
Anything, any irregularities.

27:36.629 --> 27:37.462
What are you thinking?

27:37.496 --> 27:38.696
I'm thinking it wasn't me he was after.

27:38.731 --> 27:40.698
It was our clients.

27:40.733 --> 27:43.701
That's how he stayed one step
ahead of us the whole time.

27:43.736 --> 27:46.271
He knew everything about me, about us.

27:46.305 --> 27:46.938
[Keyboard clacking]

27:46.972 --> 27:48.406
[Computer beeps]

27:48.440 --> 27:51.142
Christopher is Mr. X.

27:51.176 --> 27:54.412
Our security protocols
have been changed.

27:54.446 --> 27:56.347
We've been hacked.

27:58.350 --> 28:00.084
MARGOT: We are confident
we'll be able to meet

28:00.119 --> 28:02.787
the payment schedule this month.

28:02.821 --> 28:03.588
[Computer beeps]

28:03.622 --> 28:05.490
Yes, I know what the penalty is,

28:05.524 --> 28:07.292
but I can assure you we will absolutely

28:07.326 --> 28:09.160
make our delivery date.

28:09.194 --> 28:10.161
Thank you.

28:10.195 --> 28:10.995
[Keypad beeps]

28:11.030 --> 28:11.996
You took everything?

28:12.031 --> 28:13.631
I took everything.

28:20.339 --> 28:22.006
[Door opens]

28:22.041 --> 28:24.142
[Door closes]

28:29.573 --> 28:31.649
He took everything...
our log-ins, passwords,

28:31.674 --> 28:32.392
security codes.

28:32.409 --> 28:34.791
Everything he'd need to drain
our clients' accounts.

28:34.909 --> 28:36.936
Then why hasn't he done it yet? Look.

28:36.961 --> 28:37.727
There's no online activity,

28:37.762 --> 28:39.496
and he hasn't touched the accounts.

28:39.530 --> 28:40.497
And I've re-encrypted our data

28:40.531 --> 28:42.666
so the codes he stole
won't do him any good.

28:42.700 --> 28:45.135
So, can we start drinking now?

28:45.169 --> 28:47.471
Alice and I still have a
few hundred phone calls

28:47.505 --> 28:48.405
- to make tonight.
- No, Val.

28:48.439 --> 28:50.907
If we tell our clients,
they will fire us.

28:50.942 --> 28:53.477
Nobody stays with a security
firm that has been hacked.

28:53.511 --> 28:55.846
We have an obligation to our clients.

28:55.880 --> 28:57.414
Yes, but Christopher
hasn't actually used

28:57.448 --> 28:58.448
any of the information he stole.

28:58.483 --> 28:59.516
All of which is obsolete now.

28:59.550 --> 29:01.618
So, why don't we continue
to monitor the accounts,

29:01.652 --> 29:04.421
and then when Christopher makes
his move, we'll be there.

29:04.455 --> 29:06.756
Allie, we were there the last
time Christopher made his move.

29:06.791 --> 29:08.792
But we know who he is now.

29:08.826 --> 29:11.061
We know who we're looking for.

29:16.067 --> 29:19.803
[Siren wailing]

29:54.672 --> 29:57.007
So, I took all of our Mr. X stuff,

29:57.041 --> 29:58.308
and I put it into a comprehensive

29:58.342 --> 29:59.242
Christopher Hall timeline.

29:59.277 --> 30:01.645
Guys, there's a Jules
Dao here to see you.

30:01.679 --> 30:02.879
Jules Dao?

30:02.914 --> 30:03.914
No idea.

30:03.948 --> 30:05.348
He says he's from the FBI.

30:05.383 --> 30:07.050
At least, I think that's what he said.

30:07.084 --> 30:08.418
He has a really strong French accent.

30:08.452 --> 30:10.520
Okay, thanks, Robin. We'll be right out.

30:12.523 --> 30:13.390
Did you tell anyone about the hack?

30:13.424 --> 30:14.391
Of course not.

30:14.425 --> 30:16.426
Because if the feds know,
then our clients know.

30:16.460 --> 30:18.261
Maybe the feds should know. Maybe
they could actually help us.

30:18.296 --> 30:19.563
I don't think he's here to help us.

30:19.597 --> 30:20.230
He might be here to arrest us.

30:20.264 --> 30:21.131
We didn't call the clients.

30:21.165 --> 30:22.699
We're gonna look like co-conspirators.

30:23.968 --> 30:26.036
Okay, just don't say anything.

30:26.070 --> 30:26.836
Just let me do the talking.

30:26.871 --> 30:27.837
Okay.

30:34.979 --> 30:35.946
Jules Dao?

30:35.980 --> 30:37.614
Alice Vaughan.

30:37.648 --> 30:38.515
[African French accent] Hi.

30:38.549 --> 30:40.283
This is my partner, Valerie Anderson.

30:40.318 --> 30:41.117
Jules Dao.

30:41.152 --> 30:42.619
From the FBI?

30:42.653 --> 30:46.590
Well, Interpol originally, now the FBI.

30:46.624 --> 30:48.024
What the hell is that accent?

30:48.059 --> 30:50.260
French and African.

30:51.963 --> 30:53.530
Burkina Faso.

30:53.564 --> 30:54.464
How do you know that?

30:54.498 --> 30:59.536
I'm reading his lips.

30:59.570 --> 31:04.641
I've come to ask for your
assistance in finding this man.

31:04.675 --> 31:07.277
He is wanted for
intellectual property theft,

31:07.311 --> 31:11.281
burglary... fraud.

31:11.315 --> 31:14.384
We have no clear photos,
nor do we have a name,

31:14.418 --> 31:16.953
but I've tracked him across
Europe for two years,

31:16.988 --> 31:22.125
and now I believe he's here and
that you are tracking him, too.

31:23.427 --> 31:27.230
He stole nearly $5 million from
two of your clients this year.

31:27.265 --> 31:28.064
Actually...

31:28.099 --> 31:29.666
You think the man you're looking for

31:29.700 --> 31:30.600
is the man we're looking for?

31:30.635 --> 31:32.502
And I was hoping we could work together.

31:32.536 --> 31:36.673
Unfortunately, we can't
disclose any client information

31:36.707 --> 31:38.775
without consulting them first.

31:41.312 --> 31:44.481
So...

31:44.515 --> 31:47.684
Of course.

31:47.718 --> 31:53.256
But, please, the sooner we talk,
the better for all of us.

31:55.026 --> 31:57.627
[Chuckles]

32:02.733 --> 32:04.167
We should have told him.

32:04.201 --> 32:05.068
Val...

32:05.102 --> 32:07.370
He's been after Christopher for years.

32:07.405 --> 32:08.371
He can help us.

32:08.406 --> 32:14.344
I am not going to sit in
his supervisor's office

32:14.378 --> 32:16.880
telling a roomful of smug FBI agents

32:16.914 --> 32:18.615
what happened to me...

32:18.649 --> 32:21.651
what I let happen to me.

32:21.686 --> 32:23.286
I'm not gonna do that.

32:24.855 --> 32:28.625
[Elevator bell dings]

32:28.659 --> 32:31.695
Just give me till the end of the day.

32:31.729 --> 32:33.396
I'll find something.

32:33.431 --> 32:37.667
♪

33:16.640 --> 33:18.808
[Tires screech]

33:36.761 --> 33:38.895
[Grunting]

33:39.997 --> 33:42.732
[Car alarm blaring]

34:00.251 --> 34:04.587
Now are you ready to talk?

34:12.188 --> 34:13.621
You've been following me?

34:13.656 --> 34:16.891
Was that his car?

34:19.496 --> 34:21.597
Who is he to you?

34:23.547 --> 34:25.482
Did he take something from you?

34:27.585 --> 34:30.853
If you tell me, I can help you.

34:33.061 --> 34:36.630
You can't help me, Agent Dao.

34:44.739 --> 34:46.706
So, what do we know?

34:46.742 --> 34:48.609
VALERIE: We know Christopher
stole our security data,

34:48.643 --> 34:50.177
our clients' data.

34:50.322 --> 34:51.355
DANNY: All of which we've changed.

34:51.389 --> 34:53.125
But he had to know we were
gonna change it, right?

34:53.150 --> 34:53.949
So, why steal it?

34:53.983 --> 34:55.306
Maybe that's not what he was after.

34:55.344 --> 34:56.204
What else did he get?

34:56.228 --> 34:58.963
Everything... all our
contacts, e-mails, calendars.

34:58.998 --> 35:00.375
So he knows who our clients are.

35:00.400 --> 35:01.867
But he's always known
who our clients are.

35:01.902 --> 35:03.402
He got to us through Seth Hamilton.

35:05.405 --> 35:07.373
What if he didn't?

35:07.407 --> 35:10.509
What if he's getting to Seth through us?

35:12.813 --> 35:14.947
I don't know how I didn't see it before.

35:14.981 --> 35:18.584
Tonight Seth Hamilton will
announce a new technology

35:18.618 --> 35:20.753
that will generate billions of dollars.

35:20.787 --> 35:22.888
Christopher is going to steal it,

35:22.923 --> 35:25.157
and I know how he's gonna do it.

35:29.096 --> 35:32.431
We vetted everyone invited
to the launch tonight.

35:32.466 --> 35:34.633
Christopher is gonna use the
information that he stole

35:34.668 --> 35:38.537
from us to become one of those people...

35:38.572 --> 35:41.040
giving him direct access to
one of our biggest clients.

35:41.074 --> 35:43.976
Seth Hamilton? Andrew Merrick.

35:44.010 --> 35:45.745
I... Dr. Merrick?

35:45.779 --> 35:47.713
[Chuckles] This is... I thought...

35:47.748 --> 35:49.115
I-I was told you couldn't make it.

35:49.149 --> 35:50.616
My trip to Stockholm was postponed.

35:50.650 --> 35:51.650
I hope it's all right.

35:51.685 --> 35:54.987
Of course. It's a pleasure
to finally meet you.

35:55.021 --> 35:56.322
From what my advisors tell me,

35:56.356 --> 35:57.556
the pleasure is about to be mine.

35:57.591 --> 35:59.992
Uh, would you like to see for yourself?

36:00.026 --> 36:02.595
Please.

36:02.629 --> 36:05.231
So, you studied with Professor Gavalas?

36:05.265 --> 36:06.432
- I did.
- Yeah?

36:06.466 --> 36:09.502
A long time ago, back in 1992.

36:09.536 --> 36:12.738
Oh, wow. What was he like in '92?

36:12.773 --> 36:16.776
Well...

36:16.810 --> 36:18.511
I remember he never tired of telling me

36:18.545 --> 36:20.679
how little I actually knew
about chemical engineering.

36:20.714 --> 36:23.315
[Laughs] He still says that to me.

36:23.350 --> 36:26.519
Oh, sorry. Would you mind?

36:26.553 --> 36:28.454
You might want to take off your shoes.

36:29.723 --> 36:31.157
[Sighs]

36:32.772 --> 36:35.307
I wasn't looking for investors at first.

36:35.342 --> 36:38.444
But without them, a scalable
version would take years.

36:38.478 --> 36:40.479
And, as you know, with the drought,

36:40.513 --> 36:42.147
we don't have years.

36:42.182 --> 36:45.084
Super-easy to use.

36:45.118 --> 36:46.151
Hmm?

36:46.186 --> 36:50.756
The membrane... eh?... removes
all the salt and dirt

36:50.790 --> 36:55.794
and whatever we've been
poisoning the fish with...

36:55.829 --> 36:59.131
allowing you... to drink it.

37:02.469 --> 37:04.136
I'll go first if you want.

37:04.170 --> 37:06.305
No, no, no. I believe you.

37:11.144 --> 37:12.945
A free-radical graft polymerization

37:12.979 --> 37:15.014
of acrylic acid on a ceramic membrane.

37:15.048 --> 37:16.281
The secret formula.

37:16.316 --> 37:17.349
Can I show you the specs?

37:17.384 --> 37:19.151
Please.

37:22.522 --> 37:24.723
Sir, they're ready.

37:24.758 --> 37:27.226
[Sighs] Sorry.

37:27.260 --> 37:29.461
I hate having to play host.

37:29.496 --> 37:30.529
All right. Give me 10 minutes?

37:30.563 --> 37:31.530
Take all the time you need.

37:31.564 --> 37:32.431
Thanks.

37:33.867 --> 37:34.967
Oh, allow me.

37:35.001 --> 37:37.269
Oh, thanks. [Grunts]

37:40.840 --> 37:43.475
[Sighs]

37:43.510 --> 37:45.544
[Sea gulls squawking]

37:47.013 --> 37:48.514
[Laughter]

37:48.548 --> 37:51.350
But I made the drive again
a couple years ago.

37:51.384 --> 37:54.720
And this time, I couldn't stop
thinking that I was in trouble.

37:54.754 --> 37:57.256
We are in trouble.

37:57.290 --> 37:59.591
The drought is crippling our state.

37:59.626 --> 38:02.995
So I thought, "Why not let our
state cripple the drought?"

38:03.029 --> 38:05.564
[Cheers and applause]

38:05.598 --> 38:06.865
Did you get it?

38:06.900 --> 38:08.253
I got it.

38:08.324 --> 38:10.225
Partnering with a
desalination research team...

38:10.259 --> 38:12.026
Good. 'Cause I am single-handedly

38:12.061 --> 38:13.728
setting back the race in this outfit.

38:13.753 --> 38:16.128
Meet you out front.

38:16.215 --> 38:17.525
...I began work on Seaclarity

38:17.575 --> 38:19.876
at my lab in Santa
Monica four years ago,

38:19.911 --> 38:22.145
drawing inspiration from
the nicitating membranes

38:22.180 --> 38:24.314
found in fish and reptiles.

38:24.349 --> 38:26.383
Acrylic acid on a ceramic membrane,

38:26.417 --> 38:29.653
we can successfully
filter out salt, dirt,

38:29.687 --> 38:32.255
and all other saltwater
particles into clean,

38:32.290 --> 38:33.657
drinkable H20!

38:33.691 --> 38:36.793
[Cheers and applause]

38:39.764 --> 38:40.530
Uh, sorry, everybody.

38:40.565 --> 38:41.932
What the hell?

38:41.966 --> 38:43.266
It looks like, uh, we seem
to have blown a fuse here.

38:43.301 --> 38:44.401
Uh, one second.

38:44.435 --> 38:46.336
Just keep drinking. I'm sure
everything will be fine.

38:48.773 --> 38:52.008
Check the house. Make sure
we've got the exits covered.

38:52.043 --> 38:54.745
[Bob Moses' "Tearing Me Up" plays]

39:00.284 --> 39:03.520
♪ Let me tell you about
a little situation ♪

39:03.554 --> 39:05.522
REGGIE: You almost got us caught.

39:05.556 --> 39:08.592
You stood there like you were
about to ask her to dance.

39:08.626 --> 39:10.293
I was looking for an escape route.

39:10.328 --> 39:12.362
You were looking at her,
and you need to stop.

39:12.397 --> 39:15.565
[Sighs] If Margot finds out...

39:15.600 --> 39:20.303
You know how she is, Ben.

39:20.338 --> 39:21.872
She'll kill both of you.

39:21.906 --> 39:24.741
No, she won't.

39:24.776 --> 39:26.743
She'll have you do it.

39:26.778 --> 39:28.712
♪ She said, "No need to be
looking over your shoulder ♪

39:28.746 --> 39:30.380
♪ When you could just come over ♪

39:30.415 --> 39:33.283
♪ And we can work this out just fine" ♪

39:33.317 --> 39:34.184
[Elevator bell dings]

39:34.218 --> 39:36.253
♪ I don't know what you want from me ♪

39:36.287 --> 39:37.954
- What's our status?
- SOPHIE: We're in.

39:37.989 --> 39:39.556
What does that mean? What is she doing?

39:39.590 --> 39:40.724
She's a hacker. She's hacking.

39:40.758 --> 39:42.159
I thought she was a lawyer.

39:42.193 --> 39:42.993
A lawyer who worked for Anonymous.

39:43.027 --> 39:45.295
I asked her to build a backup plan

39:45.329 --> 39:46.596
into the thumb drive we gave Seth.

39:46.631 --> 39:48.265
Isn't hacking illegal, counselor?

39:48.299 --> 39:50.767
Not if I'm just taking back what
was ours in the first place.

39:50.802 --> 39:54.938
♪ If you're a joker then I'm a fool ♪

39:54.972 --> 39:56.440
♪ I guess there's no catching up ♪

39:56.474 --> 39:58.341
MARGOT: I don't understand.
What's happening?

39:58.376 --> 40:00.076
♪ To you

40:03.781 --> 40:06.917
What's happening is we just got conned.

40:08.186 --> 40:09.152
How?

40:09.187 --> 40:10.287
I have no idea.

40:10.321 --> 40:12.355
They hit all our offshore accounts

40:12.390 --> 40:16.193
and left us with nothing... not a cent.

40:16.227 --> 40:18.161
And our benefactor is expecting payment.

40:18.196 --> 40:20.030
If we don't pay...

40:20.064 --> 40:23.166
♪ 'Cause you've got all my attention ♪

40:23.201 --> 40:24.034
♪ I won't lie ♪

40:24.068 --> 40:25.335
Fix it.

40:25.369 --> 40:28.371
- ♪ You're tearing me up ♪
- [Door opens]

40:28.406 --> 40:30.307
♪ And I'm trying to
tell your intention ♪

40:30.341 --> 40:32.275
[Door slams]

40:32.310 --> 40:36.279
♪ When you lie you're tearing me up ♪

40:36.314 --> 40:40.317
♪ If you don't want my affection ♪

40:40.351 --> 40:43.787
♪ You won't mind, you're tearing me up ♪

41:06.344 --> 41:08.478
[Keys jingling]

41:14.452 --> 41:19.055
[Mail thuds]

41:19.090 --> 41:21.124
[Keys clatter]

41:23.761 --> 41:25.829
Hello?

41:51.322 --> 41:56.259
♪ I don't know what you want from me ♪

41:56.294 --> 42:00.463
♪ So careless in my company

42:00.498 --> 42:04.568
♪ Oh, if all that you say is true ♪

42:04.602 --> 42:09.406
♪ There'll be no getting over you ♪

42:09.440 --> 42:11.908
All right, Christopher.

42:11.943 --> 42:14.477
You want to play?

42:14.512 --> 42:16.413
Let's play.

42:16.438 --> 42:22.243
♪ I guess there's no
catching up to you ♪

